This is Roundtable, a collaborative AI beta reader tool for fiction writers.

Tech stack:
- Backend: FastAPI (Python), OpenAI API (GPT-4o-mini), Supabase (Postgres)
- Frontend: React with Tailwind CSS
- Auth: Google OAuth via Supabase

Key architecture:
- 5 AI reader personas process manuscript sections independently in parallel
- Each reader has isolated structured memory (plot events, predictions, character notes)
- Readers output inline JSON annotations tied to line numbers
- An Editor AI synthesizes all reader reactions into a summary report
- Frontend displays annotations as margin dots on the manuscript text

When making changes:
- Always handle async errors with try/except and timeouts
- Never let one reader's failure crash the other readers' pipelines
- Keep reader prompts concise — compressed prompts for section 2+
- Test with a short 3-section manuscript before deploying